      delta_list.append(calculate_delta(model, i))
      delta = aggregate(delta_list)
      model.update(delta)
      send_model(model)
#+END_SRC

* Types of FL
Based on data features and distribution FL can be categorized into two types
- Horizontal Federated Learning ::
  All the client have the same feature but their distribution may vary
- Vertical Federated Learning ::
  The features themselves are different among clients. They will be linked by some identifier
  
* Challenges and Solutions
There are three places for challenges to occur
- Client
- Server
- Communication

** Client
- Domain Shift
  - Due to the heterogeneity of the data it may take time for the global model to converge and even if it does it may have worse
    performance for some clients.
  - The paper highlights many ways to solve this. But they can be classified into the following types
    - Some version of local fine-tuning
    - Domain Adaptation
    - Image Harmonization
- Limited Datasets and labels
  - To mitigate poorly labeled and small datasets the following techniques are used
    - Contrast Learning
    - Multitask learning
    - Weakly-supervised learning
    - Knowledge Distillation
    - Data Synthesis
- Heterogeneous Environments
  - The difference in the compute resources between clients can hamper with synchronization and cause clients to be idle in
    case of a bottleneck
  - To solve this semi-synchronous methods have been developed

** Server
- Weight aggregation
  - Finding an optimal way to aggregate the weights taking into consideration the amount of importance to give to each client
- Domain Shift
  - Instead of dealing with domain shift at the client's end it can also be tackled at the server end
- Adversary detection
  - There may be situations in which a adversary can try to sabotage the learning process by sending faulty updates
  - The server has to be able to identify any anomalous updates

** Communication
- Privacy
  - There have been studies where the original data was able to be reconstructed using just the updates. So measures such as
    differential privacy has to be used to prevent this.
- Network Overhead

  
* Benchmark
Metrics on the ADNI dataset shows that FL and its spin-offs can get close to 1 to 5%  performance of centralized ML. This shows that
aggregation of disjoint updates can get equivalent performance of a centralized training with the same data. More significantly FL
allows for learning in situation that were previously not possible.

