* Shortcoming
- The paper is very well written with illustrative figure and tables. But the placement were all at the back instead of interweaving
  which I found hard.
- In the experiments they could have explained the nuances of SEN and SPE which are usually considered better for medical imaging than
  ACC due to unbalanced dataset and practical implication of false positive or negative.

* Future Research
- The paper lists several possible avenues of research.
- In addition to that many of the challenges are common to any discipline where data sharing is not possible.
- I want to explore using FL for more personal privacy things. Day by day we are giving more and more intimate data to companies.
  LLM queries, content recommendation, keyboard auto-correct and prediction (Both Apple keyboard and GBoard were trained using FL)
  and much more daily tasks can be learned using FL preserving user's privacy. 
